replyContent: Thank you for the feedback. Actually the app does not have the delete function. The textures are stored as image files in the FPS Maker folder. One question. How do you switch a switch?
replyContent: Set the two texture "State 1" and "State 2". Also set a number for the switch. On the other part create an object (eg:a monster) set the "Check switch" number the same as the switch number and set as inactive. Then if the player touches the switch, it changes its state and the objects (which are listening to this number) will be activated.
